                                IMP                 4) truncate:
-------------------------------------------------------------------

-> drop delete table and colum from the memory completely but using of truncate command we can  remove all records 
   from the table but structure remain same

-> means using of truncate we don't need to recreat table but using of drop command we have to creat table first
   there enter data.

-> truncate if faster then drop becouse it delete all records from tha table
    it's delete records from table not it not delete table.

    e.g.
    -> drop :       account; {delete karne ke liye}
    -> truncate:    delete order history  or  search history
    
    syntax:
        truncate table <tablename>;

        e.g.
            truncate student;
            {agar ander data hoga to delete ho jaye ga but table student rhega}

